36.8 Keccak256* [ME] - cryptographic hash function used in Ethereum. Keccak256 was standardised to SHA-3.
36.9 Key Derivation Function (KDF)* [ME] - also known as a password stretching algorithm, it is used by keystore format which to protect against brute-force, dictionary, or rainbow table attacks against the passphrase encryption. It repeatedly hashes the passphrase.
36.10 keystore file* [ME] - a JSON-encoded file that contains a single (randomly generated) private key, encrypted by a passphrase for extra security.
36.11 KYC* [MB] - know your customer (KYC) is the process of a business, identifying and verifying the identity of its clients. The term is also used to refer to the bank regulation which governs these activities.
